job_description: Advant-EDGE Solutions of Middle Atlantic, Inc. Our team's in-depth knowledge of the regulated waste industry makes us a valuable resource for our customers. Established in 2000, we have twenty-two (22) years of experience in the regulated medical waste industry and currently holds more than 75 government agency contracts specifically providing regulated medical waste disposal services. In over our 20 years of service, we have successfully executed several hundred service contracts many which have multiple waste streams to include, regulated medical waste, reusable and disposable sharps, non-hazardous pharmaceutical waste, trace chemotherapy waste, pathological waste, hazardous waste (RCRA), APHIS waste, universal waste, special waste and solid waste & recycling programs. ASMAI has also provided emergency response and training for the Ebola Virus and the Coronavirus. ASMAI has provided remediation and full scale (around the clock) disinfection services for our clients. For these contracts and services. we have provided the personnel, equipment, tools, materials, packaging, training, transportation, treatment and manifesting to ensure our Client's expectations are met or always exceeded. ASMAI is a nationwide contractor permitted to transport regulated medical waste in multiple states. We are proficient in providing waste solutions from cradle to grave. We manage all aspects of the waste stream from properly classifying the waste, handling the waste, packaging the waste, and the ultimate disposal of the waste. We evaluate your waste handling equipment and disposal options to provide the most efficient management of your waste. Our goal is assuring a smooth transition to our services that does not interrupt the normal flow of your staffs' workday. We initiate systems that have significant results, with simple implementations. We assist in determining containers (both reusable and disposable), selection of disposal sites, recycling centers and overall compliance. We make it easy to do it right.

Connector Street is a smart phone app that allows users to introduce two contacts or friends instantly, safely and securely without a big investment of time, effort, or resources. Because both contacts/friends know and trust the introducer, the introduction is valued and effective.   HOW IT WORKSOnce the user downloads the app and completes her profile, the app is ready to go. The user selects two contacts/friends from the contacts in her phone. (The user can also type her contacts'/friends' names and cell numbers/emails directly into the app and save that contact information into her contacts.) The user chooses the introduction type: business, social, or romantic. The user sends both contacts/friends a quick message using the app's pre-loaded introductions or creates a customized message. Once the introducer hits the Send button, the introducer's two contacts/friends receive the same introductory message, plus each receives the other's contact information. The two can begin messaging immediately from the in-app messaging system or via email or text. The app enables the introducer to save customized messages and build a library of introductions. The app stores all introductions and connections.

Healing Adults & Adolescents Residential Treatment Program (HAART) provides community-based residential care for adults. Each home must be licensed by the Division of Health Care Quality Office of Long Term Care Residents Protection and by the Delaware Medical Assistance Program {DMAP). HAART is a home that promotes healing for adults 18 years and older with severe and persistent mental illnesses, who may also have a substance abuse history. The Program gives residents an optimal chance at recovery and becoming productive members of society, while being reintegrated into their communities. HAART believes in psychosocial rehabilitation. Residents are empowered to safely live in the community with all supports needed to assist them with increasing their ability to improve their life outcomes. We center our treatment on the whole person and focus on their educational goals, vocational goals, medical needs, social/emotional needs, psychiatric needs, enhancing everyday living skills and building resiliency. Family involvement is highly encouraged and very important in our goal to assist residents with their treatment goals and integration into the community. HAART will support residents and their families with resources to remain engaged in the design and implementation of the resident's person centered recovery plan. Homes are staffed 24 hours 7 days a week. Each shift has a bachelor's level clinician to provide scheduled and as needed individual therapy as well as group therapy. A nurse is available 8 hours a day for dispensing medication and assessing medicneeds. A psychiatrist is available one day per week for psychotropic medication management and to assess other medical needs and make appropriate referrals. A master's level clinician is available for 8 hours per day to design and direct the implementation of the behavior modification person centered treatment/recovery plans.

Keywords: training, coaching, consulting At LearningCoreleadership, we shift mindset. We help providers, teams, and healthcare organizations move from the default self-focus of an inward mindset to the results-focus of an outward mindset. Through training, coaching, consulting, and our deep connection with and understanding of your health and healthcare challenges, we enable your organizations and people to achieve results that are only possible with an outward mindset, when they see the problem they don't see and become alive to the breadth of opportunities and options for achieving their goals, needs, and objectives. We help individuals, teams and organizations tackle three major challenges: Creating Collaborative Cultures Many healthcare organizations operate in a hierarchical, top-down culture that can hinder collaboration and foster conflict. The cross-functional collaboration and communication that are key to ensuring consistent clinical outcomes are undermined by the real or perceived differences in power, status, or influence that are a vestige of historical ways of operating in healthcare. We help providers, administrators and staff see their challenges differently to unleash their ability to better collaborate with and influence others. Improving Safety and Clinical Outcomes Many mistakes happen because individuals lack awareness of the impact of their actions on others within a healthcare system. With the health of patients at stake, and with increased bureaucratic scrutiny and oversight, improving safety and clinical outcomes is critically important. Our work helps overcome the many challenges in implementing process improvement, quality and safety initiatives wrought by hyper-attention to being procedurally correct while missing the opportunity to work as a team better. Research shows that low-functioning teams make far more errors and have worse outcomes than teams that work well together. Minimizing Risk and Increasing Patient Satisfaction Reigniting employee purpose and equipping healthcare professionals with the tools to effectively collaborate and communicate is key to minimizing risk and improving patient access, flow, and satisfaction. The mindset of healthcare professionals toward patients-what researchers have termed bedside manner and patient centricity -is a critical factor in the perceptions of patients regarding the care they receive. We help healthcare professionals find the outward mindset connection to their patients and customers that invigorates the quality. confidence. and closeness of those relationships.
